p: We also investigated the composition of saturated fatty acid (SFA), MUFA, and PUFA in TG and PL of the oils (TableÂ 3). SFA and MUFA in TG of FO were significantly lower than in KO and CKO. In contrast, PUFA in TG of FO was the highest at 99.22%. Fatty acids in PL of FO was not detected, but fatty acids in PL of KO and CKO was detected. KO showed a higher MUFA content than CKO, and CKO showed a higher PUFA content.
